In a press briefing, Secretary Wilkie of the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) discussed the state of the VA and the efforts the Trump administration has made to prioritize veterans. He highlighted that the President has authorized the largest budget in the department's history and that VA healthcare has received positive ratings from patients. Wilkie also discussed the MISSION Act, which integrates VA with the American healthcare system and gives veterans more choice in their healthcare decisions. He mentioned the VA's efforts to address the opioid crisis and suicide prevention among veterans. Wilkie acknowledged ongoing challenges, such as wait times and sexual assault, and discussed the steps being taken to address them. He also mentioned the VA's efforts in cancer research and appeals modernization. Overall, he emphasized the transformation and positive changes taking place at the VA under the Trump administration.